+# ADR 0001 — Typed funnel conversion-rate capability
+
+- **Status:** Accepted
+- **Date:** 2026-05-27
+- **Area:** `src/features/placements`
+
+## Context
+
+`src/features/placements/data.ts` exposes `funnel: FunnelStage[]` (Sourced →
+Replied → Phone screened → Background OK → Interview booked → Hired), rendered by
+`FunnelCard.tsx`. The card previously showed only raw counts and a relative bar
+width (`count / funnel[0].count`), guarded by `funnel[0]?.count ?? 1` — which
+silently mis-scales a zero-count funnel. There was **no conversion math** at all.
+
+Funnel data is static and presentational (no DB/API) on Next 16 / React 19 /
+strict TS 6. Naive division leaks `NaN` (0/0), `Infinity` (n/0), or values
+`> 100%` (dirty data where a later stage exceeds an earlier one) into the UI. The
+repo had no test runner.
+
+## Decision
+
+- New **pure, typed** module `src/features/placements/lib/conversion.ts` exposing
+  `computeFunnelConversion(funnel)`. It lives feature-local because the funnel
+  shape is placement-specific; `src/lib` stays reserved for cross-cutting code.
+- Output types `StageConversion` / `FunnelConversion`: per-stage `stepPct`
+  (vs. previous stage, `null` for the first stage), per-stage `overallPct`
+  (vs. top of funnel), plus a funnel-level sourced→hired `overallPct`.
+- A single `safePct(numerator, denominator)` helper is the **only** division
+  site: denominator `<= 0` → `0`, non-finite → `0`, result clamped to **[0, 100]**.
+  No NaN/Infinity/overflow can reach the UI by construction.
+- `FunnelCard` renders each stage's step-conversion via the existing
+  `formatPercent` (`@/lib/format`) and the overall sourced→hired rate in the
+  header; the bar width now uses the clamped `overallPct`.
+- **Testing:** Node built-in `node:test` + `node:assert/strict` (Node 24 native
+  TS) — **zero new dependencies**. Added an `npm test` script. Required
+  `allowImportingTsExtensions: true` in tsconfig; type-only imports use
+  `import type` so they fully erase at runtime (an empty `import {}` would
+  otherwise trigger Node's ESM resolver and fail).
+
+## Consequences
+
+- (+) Correct, centralized conversion; UI protected from NaN/Infinity/overflow;
+  first test runner in the repo with no new dependencies.
+- (−) Clamping to 100% hides genuinely dirty data (later stage > earlier).
+  Acceptable for a dashboard; flagged as a follow-up.
+- New convention: type-only relative imports use `import type`; test files use
+  explicit `.ts` extensions on value imports; app code keeps `@/` / extensionless
+  imports.
+
+## Verification (this run)
+
+- `node --test` → **6/6 pass**: empty funnel · first-stage null/100% · zero
+  top-of-funnel (no NaN/Inf) · mid-funnel zero (no Infinity) · later>earlier
+  clamped to 100% · single-stage.
+- `tsc --noEmit` → **exit 0** (whole project).
+
+## Follow-up (unscoped, future ADR)
+
+Replace the silent `> 100%` clamp with a surfaced data-quality warning so dirty
+funnel data is visible rather than masked. Estimated ~2 points when prioritized.
+

